research_municipality_step.notes: Irvington Township, NJ operates under the Faulkner Act (Mayor-Council form of government). The Mayor and three at-large council members are elected together, and two years later, the four ward council members are elected. Council members serve staggered four-year terms. The current Mayor is Tony Vauss, whose term ends on June 30, 2026. The Township Council consists of seven members: four ward council members and three at-large council members.
